text.0: Twitter has added warning labels to nine of President Trump’s post-election tweets, cautioning the messages “might be misleading.” They are misleading, and in some cases, false. We look at all nine. https://t.co/IrJPtEbVxc #FactCHAT
text.1: A video from a livestream of the vote-counting process in a PA county shows election workers transcribing votes from damaged ballots so they could be scanned and recorded. Social media users baseless claim it is evidence of voter fraud. https://t.co/GxPfGUBOJz #FactCHAT
